aa(lp67
VI got drawn into the honeybee world
p68
aVcompletely by a fluke.
p69
aVI was 18 years old and bored,
p70
aVand I picked up a book in the library on bees
p71
aVand I spent the night reading it.
p72
aVI had never thought about insects
p73
aVliving in complex societies.
p74
aVIt was like the best of science fiction come true.
p75
aVAnd even stranger, there were these people,
p76
aVthese beekeepers, that loved their bees like they were family,
p77
aVand when I put down the book, I knew I had to see this for myself.
p78
aVSo I went to work for a commercial beekeeper,
p79
aVa family that owned 2,000 hives of bees in New Mexico.
